      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEATHESTARS (2) worked and faded when resuming in the Bonanza at Melton but has trialled nicely twice since, winning his latest hitout here so he should have come on. Now with the Peter Rixon yard and won at this circuit and distance last season before finishing close to the placegetters in The Eureka. Should get his chance from the low draw. SOHO GUNSLINGER (7) has been tackling the good four-year-olds, twice finishing midfield in Listed races before racing wide in the Chariots of Fire. He will find this easier. COASTAL DRIVE (10) draws wide again but comes back in grade off the Hondo Grattan and had missed by a nose here prior. Races well third up so should be at his peak. SINABUN (11) draws widest but has won when third-up before so should be peaking following two solid efforts since a spell.",
